{"label": "reporter-direct", "event": {"type": "agent.message", "text": "Now I'll write the report following both the report-format and house-style skills:\n\nREPORTFMTOK\n\n**ADK sub_agents**\n\nSummary: A coordinator delegates to sub-agents by spawning specialized agents with self-contained task descriptions, then synthesizes their independent results back into user-facing responses.\n\nDetails:\n- **Task Definition**: The coordinator creates an agent using `create_agent(agent_name, task)`, providing a self-contained task description that includes all context, constraints, and data the sub-agent needs\u2014since sub-agents cannot access the coordinator's conversation history.\n- **Independent Execution**: Each sub-agent runs in its own thread in parallel, working autonomously without requiring handoffs or approval from the coordinator.\n- **Result Synthesis**: When sub-agents complete, the coordinator receives their replies as events, then synthesizes the findings into a coherent response for the user rather than relaying raw sub-agent output verbatim.\n\n*Trace tag: REPORTER-AGENT-OK*\n\nHOUSESTYLEOK"}}
